items.title: Marisnick departs with apparent hand injury
items.summary: Jake Marisnick departed Wednesday's game against the Angels with an apparent hand injury after sliding into second base, trying to stretch a single into a double. He was thrown out and left the game shortly thereafter.

items.title: Dodgers to play Barnes, Hernandez more
items.summary: With a half-month remaining in the regular season, the Dodgers' taste for experimentation continues to dissipate. Manager Dave Roberts said Kiké Hernandez will play against lefties going forward. Austin Barnes, usually in the lineup against lefties, will catch more frequently against right-handed pitching.

items.title: Oberg returns to form at right time for Rockies
items.summary: Rockies righty reliever Scott Oberg has had plenty of rough performances -- enough that he was sent down to Triple-A Albuquerque for two weeks in August. But interestingly, the last difficult game was the catalyst for his current hot streak.
